The paper deals with imitation learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The use of policy optimization and evaluation in an online learning setting suggests that the paper may belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with stability conditions and convergence, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of policy sequences and optimization suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also deals with image-based imitation learning, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with control problems, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control).
